**Vision alignment:** Carried from Round 1 without modification. The adversarial prior was that this PR ships sensing + schema + dispatch in a single pass when the design spec explicitly named the sensing protocol as Phase 0 — a prerequisite requiring separate design specification before any schema or dispatch changes. The prior was partially confirmed (dead constant implied a gate that didn't exist, suggesting the sensing implementation was not fully reviewed against its own spec) and partially disconfirmed (clean pure-function design, mandatory rationale enforcement, correct non-fatal wrapping). The questioning is on record in learnings.md (PR #906 entry). The implementation is sound; the gap fixes close the blocking issues.
